parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause unexpected shutdowns, loss of critical systems, and increased risk of accidents.
Door actuator failure can cause doors to malfunction, leading to safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: doors not responding to key fob or internal buttons
doors stuck in open or closed position.

symptoms: and failure to respond to inputs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause accidents and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sun Roof and Water Leak Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks can cause electrical system failures, corrosion, and safety hazards.
Engine failure can cause accidents, especially on highways.
The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to seize or become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel seizes or becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls hard to one side
the steering feels like it "pauses" or is harder to turn
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver when making turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent steering issues can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels soft or spongy
the steering wheel sticks to the left or right
the steering wheel has a delayed return to its normal position
the vehicle is difficult to steer at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause the vehicle's systems to malfunction, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The instrument panel and navigation screens shut off and turn back on
the cruise control lever on the steering column flickers off and on
the radio instrument panel shuts off and reboots.
